By far one of the best chinese fast food takeouts in NYC.  Ive been here twice, both time ordering general tso chicken, and it beats gourmet food in that aspect. A little greasy but absolutely delicious, if youre in this part of brooklyn check them out.

I hate to write a 1 star review during times of COVID when all restaurants are hurting, but I don't think fraudulent businesses should continue to operate. We ordered a simple dish costing over $8. After handing over a $50 bill and apologizing that we unfortunately don't have a smaller bill, the cashier provided change as if we had given him a $20. He proceeded to take out a crumpled $20 bill claiming that that's what we paid even though we handed over a crisp $50. The cashier claimed they don't have security video footage and there was nothing we could do to prove otherwise. This is highly disappointing as we have ordered from them periodically over the past 30 years or so and have always had a good experience with the staff and have enjoyed the food. The new people working there cannot be trusted.

I have ordered from here in the past and, while nothing to write home about, they have decent food.  Today was my first time ordering from this spot since COVID-19. I was extremely disappointed that they did not take credit cards and/or did not remind us that they only take cash, even with the current pandemic. I was forced to used a filthy looking ATM machine, and I am writing this review especially for folks who might want to order from them.  Ask for the amount on the phone, and bring exact cash if possible to pickup, so you have nothing to put back into your wallet.  I think it is rather negligent of the business to not be mindful of that small step, devoid of which they are potentially putting a lot of people in danger.
